<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>Tyrel Hiebert | Photos &amp; Code</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/normalizeSmall.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/mainstyle_backup.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/secondarystyle.css">
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Khula:800|Slabo+27px" rel="stylesheet">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
</head>
<body>

  <header id="top">
    <div id="topColor"></div>
    <a href="index.html" id="logo">
      <h1>Tyrel Hiebert</h1>
      <h2>Photos &amp; Code</h2>
    </a>
    <nav>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="index.html">Portfolio</a></li>
        <li><a href="about.html">About</a></li>
        <li><a href="#contactLink">Contact</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
    <div id="bottomColor"></div>
  </header>
<!-- CONTENT -->
  <div id="wrapper">
  <section  class="floatFix">
    <img src="images/profilePic2.jpg" alt="profile picture of tyrel hiebert" class="profilePic">
    <h3>About</h3>
    <p>Hi, my name is Tyrel Hiebert. This is my photography and web design portfolio where i will share all of my favorite work. When I am not making photos or writing code, I enjoy riding my bike or sitting in a local coffee shop with a good book.</p>
    <h3 id="whatIDo">What I Do</h3>
    <p>Currently, I am a student at <a href="http://teamtreehouse.com/tyrelhiebert" target="_blank">Treehouse</a>, learning Responsive Front End Development. I enjoy designing and building clean and intuitive W3C valid HTML5 and CSS3 websites and user interfaces.</p>
    <div id="codeBadge">
      <img src="images/badgeHTML5.png" class="codeBadge" alt="html5 badge">
      <img src="images/badgeCSS3.png" class="codeBadge" alt="css3 badge">
    </div>
    <p>If you would like to get in touch with me, the best way is via email.</p>
    <p><a href="mailto:tyrel.hiebert@gmail.com">Tyrel.Hiebert@gmail.com</a></p>
  </section>
  <section id="contactSection">
    <div id="contactLink"></div>
    <h3>Contact Info</h3>
    <p>You can contact me here:</p>
    <form action="#" method="POST" name="contactMe">
      <input type="text" name="name" value="name"><br>
      <input type="email" name="email" value="email"><br>
      <input type="text" name="inquiry" value="inquiry"><br>
      <textarea name="message">message</textarea><br>
      <input type="submit" value="Send">
    </form>
  </section>
